title: [Weekly Report] Project Manager for September 17-23rd (A.G.)
body:
# Project Manager Weekly Report

## Weekly Checklist

- [x] Created a weekly report for the group project
- [x] Moved brainstorming documents into repo
- [x] Collect potential data sources for Adobe Flash Media and paste the links into the repo
- [x] Complete questions for Pt 2
- [x] Draft project proposal
- [x] Complete and close issue

## Weekly Summary:

> What were the goals for this week for the group project?
- Find data sources or archives for Adobe flash media
- Refine our research question
- Brainstorm how to scale our research, and how to tackle access limitations (ex: Flashpoint only having a search function)

> What has been accomplished?
- **Data sources found**: We will be using Flashpoint Archive to source our pre-2011 and post-2011 Flash games
- **Decided our research question**: "What patterns in the portrayals of gender arise in Adobe Flash games pre-2011 and post-2011?"

> Any problems or issues that need resolving?
- Ellis can't push onto the repo, and we don't know why?
     - Will be figuring out in class on Tuesday
- Need to figure out how we will parse through Flashpoint archive, given that the games are not indexed in pages or categorized into any game category

## Next Week's Goals:

> What are the goals for the upcoming week?
- Determine how we will collect data through Flashpoint archive
- Figure out how to run Flashpoint from our local machines
- Test some of the games in the archive, check which ones work
- See if we can webscrape some of the tabular data

> Who is assigned to what tasks?
- Next PM: Divya Jain

*Optional additional information*

- Anything else to highlight?
